The Vice President, Kamala Harris, spoke at the HRC Dinner at the Walter E. Washington Convention Center in Washington, D.C. She began by addressing the recent attack on Paul Pelosi, expressing her support for Speaker Pelosi and her family. Harris praised the work of HRC and its leaders in fighting for civil and human rights. She emphasized the importance of coalitions and the power of working together. Harris highlighted the progress made by the Biden administration in protecting LGBTQ+ rights, including expanding protections, fighting HIV/AIDS, and appointing LGBTQ+ leaders. She acknowledged the challenges faced by the LGBTQ+ community, such as hate crimes, violence against transgender individuals, and discrimination. Harris criticized extremist leaders who have pushed for anti-LGBTQ+ and anti-reproductive rights legislation. She called for unity and the need to build coalitions to defend freedom and equality. Harris urged support for the Equality Act, Respect for Marriage Act, Freedom to Vote Act, John Lewis Voting Rights Advancement Act, and protecting Roe v. Wade. She quoted Harvey Milk, emphasizing the importance of making voices heard and encouraged participation in the upcoming election. Harris concluded by expressing gratitude and hope for a better future.